The paper deals with lossless compression of individual sequences using finite-state machines, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of empirical cumulant generating functions and entropy measures also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the extension of the results to compression with side information indicates a possible relevance to signal processing (cs.SI).
